Installed-Size: 256
Maintainer: Dennis Kaweesi <dkaweesi1@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/Lovepankie/snipping-tool
Description: Screenshot and annotation tool for Linux
 Snipping Tool is a full-featured screenshot utility for Linux Mint
 and GTK-based desktops. It works exactly like the Windows Snipping
 Tool — and better.
 .
 Features:
  * Rectangular, freeform, window, and full-screen capture modes
  * Dimming overlay with live size indicator
  * Annotation editor: pen, highlighter, arrow, shapes, text, eraser
  * Clipboard integration (auto-copy after capture)
  * Save as PNG or JPEG
  * Undo/redo support
  * Global hotkey (Ctrl+Shift+S via keybinder)
  * System tray icon with right-click menu
  * Capture delay (0–10 seconds)
